A lot of queuing but some nice views.
Oct 2024 â¢ Family
When in Paris (and if you've not done it before), the Eiffel Tower is a must see. We pre-booked for the lift to the top before embarking on our holiday and this was worth it as the queues for tickets we saw were very long indeed. It was a bit muddly working out which 'leg' to queue at and it seemed once we got through the zig-zag route, that two sides came together, so you have to kind of push your way to your spot by the first lift or you'd never get on. Short ride to the '2nd floor' and then another queue for the lift to the top. Didn't take very long for this 2nd queue and then up we were. There are some steps to take you even higher up and you get a great view of Paris. It was misty when we arrived (our tickets were 11.30am) but by the time we got up there, the mist had cleared and we had great views. Reverse the queuing to get back down again.

We didn't really walk around the gardens at all and it looked like some work was being done on a large section which was closed off.

Eiffel Tower â A Must-See, but Be Prepared for Crowds!
Mar 2024 â¢ Family
The Eiffel Tower is undoubtedly one of the most iconic landmarks in the world, and the views from the top are absolutely breathtaking. You can see all of Paris laid out before you, and the experience of standing at such a famous spot is unforgettable. I

However, be prepared for the crowds. The tower attracts thousands of visitors every day, and while that's to be expected given its popularity, it can feel a bit overwhelming at times. The lines can be long, and the observation deck can get quite packed, especially during peak hours. It's worth it, but just know that you're not going to have the place to yourself.

Pro tip: Try to visit early in the morning or later in the evening to avoid the heaviest crowds.

Despite the crowds, the Eiffel Tower's status as a symbol of Paris and its incredible views make it an experience worth having.
